President of the European Commission Ms von der Leyen looked visibly uncomfortable broaching the subject of Ukrainian membership to the EU ahead of today's summit. After a brief stumble, she admitted that they would discuss the possibility of Ukraine joining the EU without specifying a position. Ukraine and the EU share "a common destiny", she added. BBC Brussels correspondent Jessica Parker notes that the situation is "getting awkward" for the EU. French President Emmanuel Macron is bringing his 26 counterparts from around the EU to meet at the Palace of Versailles, in Paris this afternoon. The purpose of the gathering is to discuss economic and financial affairs in light of the Russian invasion of Ukraine. THIS LIVE BLOG IS NOW CLOSED - READ COVERAGE BELOW...